—ЩKarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/for.mdЩ@4a06b53c1b818e598e633e2dfe709d8043c0f6815e346bdb98ccf149dffbb7e0Єtitle: for‘ЁExamplesЪ]Print the square of each integer.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for x in [1 2 3] { print ($x * $x) }


```
Work with elements of a range.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for $x in 1..3 { print $x }


```
Number each item and print a message.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for $it in (['bob' 'fred'] | enumerate) { print $"($it.index) is ($it.item)" }


```
’ђђЪ‡Title: title: for
Path: Examples
Content:
Print the square of each integer.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for x in [1 2 3] { print ($x * $x) }


```
Work with elements of a range.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for $x in 1..3 { print $x }


```
Number each item and print a message.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> for $it in (['bob' 'fred'] | enumerate) { print $"($it.index) is ($it.item)" }


```
